OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1776330350
OL,3,CPM to meet social media bosses in
OL,4,CDowning Street after calls for under-
OL,5,C16s ban
OL,7,FIn January, Tory peer Lord Nash won a
OL,8,Fvote in the House of Lords, adding an
OL,9,Famendment to the government's
OL,10,FChildren's Wellbeing and Schools Bill,
OL,11,Fwhich would ban social media use by
OL,12,Funder-16s.
OL,14,FThe government opposed this amendment,
OL,15,Fand it was defeated by MPs in the
OL,16,FCommons on March 9.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,313,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F312A1776330350
OL,3,CPM to meet social media bosses in
OL,4,CDowning Street after calls for under-
OL,5,C16s ban
OL,7,FThe legislation is currently stuck in
OL,8,Fwhat is known as parliamentary ping-
OL,9,Fpong, with the government defeating
OL,10,Fthe amendment in the Commons, but
OL,11,Fseeing it voted back into the Bill
OL,12,Fwhen passed to the Lords.
OL,14,FIn a vote in the Commons on Wednesday,
OL,15,FMPs rejected the Lords-backed social
OL,16,Fmedia ban for a second time.
OL,18,FThey voted by 256 to 150, majority
OL,19,F106, to side with the government on
OL,20,Fits plan to tackle social media-linked
OL,21,Fharms affecting children.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
